['import sys
from math import sqrt, floor, factorial
from collections import deque, Counter
inp = sys.stdin.readline
read = lambda: list(map(int, inp().strip().split()))

def solve():
	n = int(inp()); arr = read(); c = 1;s = 0
	for i in arr:
		if i < -1:
			c *= -1
			s += abs(-1-i)
		else:
			c *= 1
			s += abs(1-i)
	s += [0, 2][c<1]
	print(s)




if __name__ == "__main__":
	solve()

["lengthA = int(input())
a = input().split(' ')
a = [int(i) for i in a]
lengthB = int(input())
b = input().split(' ')
b = [int(i) for i in b]

def binary_search(a_list, item):
    f = 0
    last = len(a_list)-1
    found = False

    while f <=last and not found:
        mid = (f+last)//2
        if a_list[mid] == item:
            found = True
        elif item < a_list[mid]:
                last = mid-1
        else:
            f = mid+1
    return found

i = 0
while i<lengthA:
    found = False
    for j in b:
        add = a[i]+j 
        if binary_search(a, add)!=True and binary_search(b, add)!=True:
            print(a[i], j)
            found = True
            break
    if found:
        break
    i+=1"]

["lengthA = int(input())
a = input().split(' ')
a = [int(i) for i in a]

b = input().split(' ')
b = [int(i) for i in b]

def binary_search(a_list, item):
    f = 0
    last = len(a_list)-1
    found = False

    while f <=last and not found:
        mid = (f+last)//2
        if a_list[mid] == item:
            found = True
        elif item < a_list[mid]:
                last = mid-1
        else:
            f = mid+1
    return found

out = ''
index_search = 0 
for i in b:
    search = (a[index_search]+i)
    if not binary_search(a,search) and not binary_search(b,search):
        out += str(a[index_search])+' '+ str(i)
        break

print(out)"]

['from functools import reduce 
n = int(input())
k = 0
zero = False
even = True
numbers = list(map(int,input().split()))
for i in range(n):
    if numbers[i] > 1:
        k += (numbers[i] - 1)
        numbers[i] = 1
    elif numbers[i] < -1:
        k += abs(numbers[i]+1)
        if even:
            even = False
        else:
            even = True
        numbers[i] = -1
    elif numbers[i] == 0:
        k += 1
        zero = True
        numbers[i]= 1

result = reduce((lambda x, y: x * y), numbers) 
if result == -1 and not zero:
        k += 2
print(k)

']

    if Array[i] > 1:

    return p
